{"word":"γεωργέω","slug":"γεωργέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γεωργέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γεωργός'><el>γεωργός</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be a husbandman, farmer</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to till, plough, cultivate</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to work at</i> a thing, <i>practise</i> it, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>agitare</el>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b>; <el>γ. ἔκ τινος</el> <i>to draw profit</i> from it, <i>live</i> by it, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}